cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.MM 

This paper deals with facial expression recognition, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of Random Forests and autoencoder networks for training and weighting the local expression predictions suggests a machine learning approach (cs.LG, cs.AI). The subjectivity of labelling expressions and the need for robustness in the face of occlusions suggest a human-computer interaction (cs.HC) aspect to the work. Finally, the use of high-level representations for describing facial expressions suggests a multimedia (cs.MM) aspect to the work.
